The max-F1 scores in Table (ref) \& (ref) are far from 100%, i.e., LMs do not generate candidate lists that correctly rank all true objects above the false ones. In particular, max-F1 will not reach 100% when correct objects are ranked too low or absent. We found that 26.90% of valid objects in a candidate list were ranked below the optimal threshold and 27.75% of valid objects were not generated at all.